Sentinel for Debian/Kali Linux
==============================

This package provides Sentinel, a protection-first web vulnerability scanner.

Installation
------------

After installation, Sentinel is available via:

1. Command line: `sentinel` or `sentinel-gui`
2. Applications menu: Web Application Analysis â†’ Sentinel Scanner

Quick Start
-----------

1. Create a consent document for authorized scanning:

   sentinel consent create \
     --target https://example.com \
     --org "Your Organization" \
     --authorized-by "Your Name" \
     --email your@email.com \
     --file consent.json

2. Run a scan:

   sentinel scan \
     --target https://example.com \
     --consent consent.json \
     --depth 10 \
     --output report.json

3. For localhost targets (no consent required):

   sentinel scan \
     --target http://localhost:3000 \
     --depth 5 \
     --safety ACTIVE

Documentation
